webpackJsonp([0x6129d2d1f92b],{510:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{wordpressWpLessons:{id:"50c0c00f-4e8a-57fb-93e1-11cc8389cc10",wordpress_id:6709,title:"Activity: Practicing CSS Part 2",slug:"activity-practicing-css-part-2",content:'<h2>Objectives and Overview</h2>\n<p>This lesson provides a <em>going further</em> activity for practicing CSS in <a href="http://thimble.mozilla.org">Thimble</a>. Make sure that you&#8217;ve completed the previous HTML lessons and activities, including the <em><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/lesson/web-development-mini-project/">Web Development Mini Project</a></em>. It&#8217;s a much higher priority to finish that project before attempting working through this lesson. Remember, you can always go back and add more content to your page using your new skills. Let&#8217;s get started!</p>\n<h3>Lesson Objectives:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Work through an intermediate CSS project on Thimble to build your CSS positioning skills</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h2 class="learn-activity">Activity: CSS Building Blocks</h2>\n<p>This activity is a good way to deepen your understanding of the relationship between <strong>&lt;div&gt; elements</strong> and CSS style. The HTML burger activity primarily utilized <strong>class selectors</strong>, whereas this activity includes more selectors such as <strong>ids</strong>.</p>\n<p>There is a lesson built into the activity, so make sure to check the notes in the project while practicing. There are some intermediate concepts about layout and position included as well. Just do your best to understand it and make sure to try everything! Remember, you can always start again by creating a new remix of the original project.</p>\n<p>Before starting, make sure that you&#8217;re logged in to Thimble.</p>\n<p>First, open this link in a new browser window: <a href="https://thimbleprojects.org/mozillalearning/198703/">https://thimbleprojects.org/mozillalearning/198703/</a></p>\n<p>Once there you&#8217;ll see the green remix button in the top right corner. Click this button to start your remix:</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6712" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-1024x506.jpg" alt="thimble css building blocks view page remix highlighted" width="625" height="309" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-1024x506.jpg 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-300x148.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-768x379.jpg 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-200x100.jpg 200w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-624x308.jpg 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-100x49.jpg 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-1-750x370.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></p>\n<p>Once you have your copy of the project, you&#8217;ll be able to see the <strong>Tutorial</strong> tab in the top right corner. There is some great information in this lesson, so check this out:</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6714" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-1024x503.jpg" alt="thimble css building blocks tutorial tab highlighted" width="625" height="307" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-1024x503.jpg 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-300x147.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-768x377.jpg 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-200x98.jpg 200w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-624x306.jpg 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-100x49.jpg 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-tutorial-750x368.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></p>\n<p>The tutorial reinforces the content from the <a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/lesson/activity-practicing-css-part-1/">previous lesson</a> about the <strong>&lt;div&gt;</strong> element and also has sections on the additional CSS properties such as display, background-color, position, and size.</p>\n<p>After you&#8217;ve read through the lesson, go ahead and start making some changes to your remix. Remember, to change each block you&#8217;ll need to find the corresponding <strong>id selector</strong> in the stylesheet.css:</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6716" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-1024x497.jpg" alt="thimble css building blocks editor and preview stylesheet div highlighted" width="625" height="303" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-1024x497.jpg 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-300x146.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-768x373.jpg 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-200x97.jpg 200w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-624x303.jpg 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-100x49.jpg 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mf-web-dev-css-remix-3-750x364.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></p>\n<p>Any changes that you would make to the <strong>#blockOne</strong>. Note that each of these blocks is an <strong>id</strong> and not a <strong>class</strong>. There can only be one unique id per page. You can test this and see what happens by trying to repeat the same id for another div.</p>\n<h2>Next Steps</h2>\n<p>This activity has lots of great selectors to experiment with. After you get the hang of it, try to add and position your own block! Remember that it would need to have its own id.</p>\n<p>After you&#8217;ve remixed this project, try to add some <strong>&lt;div&gt; elements</strong> to your <em>About Me</em> page. You can use these to create content blocks. Give it a shot and see what you come up with!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'}},pathContext:{}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---activity-practicing-css-part-2-2e7961cc3784b352ed82.js.map